The [[Amiga]] and [[Atari ST]] version use digitized sound effects.

The [[MS-DOS]] version supports 16-color [[Enhanced Graphics Adapter|EGA]] or [[Tandy-compatible]] graphics, 4-color [[Color Graphics Adapter|CGA]] graphics, and 2-color [[Hercules Graphics Card|Hercules]] graphics. Three-voice music is supported on the Tandy.

==Reception==
''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' called the game "an imaginative adventure game" with unusually good graphics and audio. It recommended the game to fans of adventures with puzzles, with the story's short length and abrupt ending the main faults.{{r|greenberg19900708}}

